{"tid":1145914,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"【科技文字獄】新版Microsoft Word將會增加「政治正確」改正功能","createTime":"2019-05-09T02:21:16.000Z","updateTime":"2019-05-15T13:14:18.000Z","uid":131691,"like":1,"dislike":44,"uniUserReply":15,"replies":[{"pid":"fe6e3e1dc517d3d735dab6328900fca09e070566","tid":1145914,"uid":131691,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-09T02:21:16.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.fastcompany.com/90346224/microsoft-word-is-getting-politically-correct\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fastcompany.com%2F90346224%2Fmicrosoft-word-is-getting-politically-correct&d=fyMqA0bs77BZF9qEbHCyfmHyg7b2nkJB6fx123wLmsI%3D&h=a2f16cb0\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.fastcompany.com/90346224/microsoft-word-is-getting-politically-correct</a><br />\n美其名 &quot;Ideas in Word&quot;，話係用AI嚟改文法，但係「唔知點解」會改埋用字係咪政治正確。<br />\nIf you tend to say &ldquo;mailman&rdquo; or Congressman&rdquo; in the generic, it might suggest you use &ldquo;mailperson&rdquo; or &ldquo;Congressperson.&rdquo; If you use the term &ldquo;gentlemen&rsquo;s agreement,&rdquo; it may suggest you use &ldquo;unspoken agreement&rdquo; instead.<br />\nIf you describe someone as a &ldquo;disabled person&rdquo; the AI would suggest &ldquo;person with a disability.&rdquo; Person-first terminology is preferred because it portrays the person as more important than the disability.<br />\n以後想寫 police dog 可能要寫 dog with mental disabilities 啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"0d75b03834af81d5aaa1d8c97305442745b3bf73","tid":1145914,"uid":92230,"like":30,"dislike":0,"score":30,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-09T02:24:07.000Z","msg":"person個son都係父權嘅表現<img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/33.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\ncongressperchild 咁先正確<img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/33.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"4f3a7e13038dd423a83e7dba4c061a073dc4a6d0","tid":1145914,"uid":66242,"like":34,"dislike":0,"score":34,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"201